utilMDE
Class StrTok

java.lang.Object
  utilMDE.StrTok

public class StrTok
extends java.lang.Object

Provides a somewhat simpler interface for tokenizing strings than does StreamTokenizer. All tokenizing is done by StreamTokenizer.

The major difference from StreamTokenizer is that all tokens are returned as strings. EOF returns a null, EOL returns an empty string. A delimiters is returned as a one-character string. Words and numbers are returned as strings. Quoted strings are also returned as strings including their quote characters (so they can easily be differentiated from words and numbers). Other differences are:

  • Automatic setup for tokenizing strings.
  • Underscores are included in identifiers (words).
  • I/O errors (which should be impossible when tokenizing strings) are converted to RuntimeExceptions so that every call doesn't have to be included in a try block.
  • Convenience functions isWord(), isQString(), and need().
  • Returned string tokens are interned for easier comparisons.

See Also:
StrTok.Error

need

public void need(java.lang.String tok)
Reads the next token and checks that it matches tok. If it does not match, calls the current error handling routine (see set_error_handler()). If it does match, just returns.

need_word

public java.lang.String need_word()
Reads the next token and checks to make sure that it is a word (id). If it is not a word, calls the error handling routine. If it is, returns the string of the word.
